The paper focuses on the development of a new dataset for human-robot interaction and navigation, which is a core topic in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The dataset includes eye gaze data, which involves computer vision techniques (cs.CV) for analysis. The paper also proposes a set of metrics to analyze the dataset, which involves machine learning and data analysis techniques (cs.LG). The dataset is designed for human-robot interaction, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social intelligence (cs.SI).
